    "actor_description": "It lands like a door closing in my face. My stomach drops and my chest goes tight-hot, like I want to protest and vanish at the same time. I can’t stop replaying the social shape of it; my attention keeps snapping back there, searching for what I did wrong. I feel smaller, edged out, and it stings in a way that makes my jaw set.",
    "description_text": "{actor} goes visibly tight and guarded—eyes flicking back as if checking a boundary, mouth pressing thin. Their posture pulls in, but there’s a brittle edge to it, like they’re fighting the urge to snap back or shut down.",
